        "subject": "LU-12441 lnet: response tracker cleanup",
        "message": "LU-12441 lnet: response tracker cleanup\n\nLNetPut/LNetGet don't need to allocate lnet_rsp_tracker. This can\nbe handled in lnet_attach_rsp_tracker().\n\nlnet_attach_rsp_tracker() can be simplified a bit.\n\nThere's an additional case where we need to detach the response\ntracker. MDs for pings use the infinite threshold on MD operations.\nAs such they aren't normally unlinkable as determined by\nlnet_md_unlinkable(). We can cover this case by checking whether the\nrefcount is zero and threshold is LNET_MD_THRESH_INF. This is moved\ninside lnet_detach_rsp_tracker(), and we also add the result of\nlnet_md_unlinkable() as a parameter to lnet_detach_rsp_tracker().\nThis allows all of the logic for determining whether the response\ntracker should be unlinked to reside in one place.\n\nCray-bug-id: LUS-7366\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I4b9499bc6327523f1e911ebc4514002511e42236\n"
      },
